So I'm settling on adding a meaningless search modifier to my Google Alerts: 

(inurl:smizzlepit | -inurl:smizzlepit)

I'll filter my Google Alerts for both "digital archive" and smizzlepit and offload those English-language results so I don't have to look at them.

I need to filter those results for non-English results only. In this case I need to filter out all results with "digital archive" in English. 

Trying to build a filter around the alert would be tough as I use "digital archive" a LOT and I'm afraid of accidental triggers.

Google Alerts lets you specify search results in any language, so theoretically I can just create an alert for "digital archive" in all languages and wait for the results, but the problem is I'll get overwhelmed with results in English, which I already monitor for.
